The sun has just set, casting a deep, ominous shadow over the ocean that looms ahead. I could almost feel the breeze, the cold, salty sea air tickling my ears.
I turn back, searching for Mira among the dark clouds of shadows. Her name was Mira – her friend since we were little and we shared everything - food, jokes, adventures. Our friendship lasted till our teenage years.
Now, after so many years of separation, her absence seems like a distant memory now. But I still miss her presence, even though she moved away decades ago, leaving all of us behind.
There, a small boat glides in and out of the water. I cautiously step towards its side, looking up at the starlit sky with excitement. I see the ship moving closer; I don’t know what they have aboard.
But then I hear a voice, soft as music from a remote place:
"Alexe!"  
Mira walks up to me, eyes wide and a hint of a smile playing around her lips, but otherwise, nothing visible. Without another word, she reaches into my backpack, pulls out a notebook, and begins to write something on it. I can hear the notes and I immediately realize they must be some form of coded message.  
Alex, who I knew barely existed until I realized Mira was there, hears the words aloud in the silence:  
"We're close."
And with that, he whispers something else:
"You're safe."

